node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Radhi Devlukia-Shetty on July 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Here's the thing, just because you THINK you deserve something doesn't make it true. When you convince yourself of that, you will take things or desire things that do not belong to you and that is a slippery slope. Sometimes we can change the reality in our minds to fit the story we want to make our actions seem justified. That's delusion. Radhi'.

node.text:
I spend a whole lot of my day on my laptop, especially since the pandemic. I didn’t even think my laptop would have any effect on the environment and it never even occurred to me. But hearing the incredible research and efforts from @dell to create the Latitude 5320 was eye opening! 
It is the 1st PC with a lid made of 21% tree-based bioplastics from tree sources and the manufacturing of these laptops reduces co2 emissions equal to 24.2 million miles driven, saves enough energy to power 5564 homes for 1 year and conserves enough water to fill 226 Olympic size pools! A little change can make a big difference! #progressmadereal #ad

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Radhi Devlukia-Shetty on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'We have to let go in order to create space to recieve more, to recieve better. There are always things we need to shed and let go of, some old we've kept in the dark corners of our mind and some new that are at the top of the pile! Letting go has to be a part of the natural cycle of life, we are so used to holding on, hording and wanting to preserve everything that we forget to let go of the things that no longer need to be part of us. Radhi'.

node.text: Take a moment to think, what do I need to let go of today!? Lemme tell you everyday I do that i come up with a wholleeeeee lot 💛 we need to stop seeing letting go as a LOSS. don't be afraid to let go and embrace what is..it's in the past for good reason it had its time now it's ti@e to Acknowledge it Appreciate it then lovingly let go 💛 #quotes #quoteoftheday
